Question 22 of 50

Your organization uses Microsoft Fabric to manage data analytics solutions. There is a need to protect sensitive data and ensure only authorized users can access it.

You need to restrict access to sensitive data across the environment.

What should you do?

Select only one answer.

Apply sensitivity labels.

This answer is correct.

Implement row-level security.


Set item-level permissions.


Implement object-level security.

This answer is incorrect.
To restrict access to sensitive data, sensitivity labels protect data and limit access to authorized users for all Fabric items. Implementing row-level security controls access to specific rows within a data store, but does not apply sensitivity labels to restrict access based on data sensitivity. Setting item-level permissions might control access to specific items but does not automatically apply sensitivity labels or control access based on data sensitivity. Similarly, object-level security is only applicable to certain items in the environment.

